In this article, President Obama emphasizes the importance of strengthening the education system in the United States. Despite the efforts to rebuild the economy and create jobs, Obama believes that providing quality education to children is crucial for the country's success in the 21st century. While Republicans in Congress are trying to cut education funding by 20%, the President remains committed to implementing reforms that give all children a first-class education and prepare them with the skills and knowledge needed to compete in the global economy. Obama will continue to fight for an educational system that helps build a strong middle class and provides the best possible opportunities for children.